Seventh Avenue, west side, from 16th to 15th Streets, showing new apartment house at 200 West 16th Street nearing completion. February 28, 1930.

Charles Curtis.

Seventh Avenue at N.E. corner of 15th Street, across excavation at S.W. corner, showing Street and Smith Building.
February 28, 1931.
P.L. Sperr, Photographer.

15th Street at N.W. corner of Seventh Avenue, and west to the middle of the block. St. Joseph's Home for the aged (1873), which is maintained by the Society of St. Vincent De Paul, adjoins the corner.
The construction work on the S.W. corner of Seventh Avenue is for a new apartment house.
1931
P.L. Sperr.

[handwritten, at bottom]:
New Apt. - 6 story - Arch draw.  Herald Tribune 1/21/40

Transportation: A beer truck moving northward on 7th Avenue. At the right is the publishing plant of Street and Smith, occupying the easterly frontage of the Avenue from W. 15th to 16th Streets.

1938

Alexander Alland

This photo is one of a series that appeared in the published volume "Portrait of N. Y." by Felix Reisenberg and Alex. Alland, IRGV.

Macmillan, pub.
title: Transportation - Beer Turck.
